### Step 7: Pull Request Description

#### 7.1 PR Description Template

**Complete PR Description Template:**

```markdown
## Task
<Brief description of the task being implemented>

## Context
<Background information about why this task is needed>
<Reference to planning document if applicable>

## Changes Implemented
<Summary of key changes made in the code>

### Added
- List of new features
- List of new files
- List of new APIs

### Modified
- List of modified features
- List of modified files

### Removed
- List of removed features (if any)
- List of removed files (if any)

## Services Affected
<Services that were modified>

### Primary Service
- **[Service Name]** - [Brief description of changes]

### Secondary Services
- **[Service Name]** - [Brief description of changes]

## Files Modified
<Summary of important files that were created or modified>

### New Files
- `path/to/new/file.ts` - Description
- `path/to/another/file.ts` - Description

### Modified Files
- `path/to/modified/file.ts` - Description of changes
- `path/to/another/file.ts` - Description of changes

## API Changes
<If APIs were added or modified>

### New Endpoints
- **METHOD /path** - Description
  - Request: Example request body
  - Response: Example response

### Modified Endpoints
- **METHOD /path** - Description of changes

### Deprecated Endpoints
- **METHOD /path** - Deprecation notice

## Database Changes
<If database schema was modified>

### New Tables
- `table_name` - Description

### Modified Tables
- `table_name` - Description of changes

### Migrations
- Migration files applied

## Event Changes
<If events were added or modified>

### New Events Published
- `event.name` - Description

### New Event Subscriptions
- `event.name` - Description of handler

## Testing Summary
<Brief summary of testing performed based on testing.md>

### Test Results
- ✅ Compilation Tests: PASS
- ✅ Startup Tests: PASS
- ✅ API Tests: PASS
- ✅ Backward Compatibility Tests: PASS
- ✅ Logic Tests: PASS
- ✅ Integration Tests: PASS
- ✅ Code Quality Tests: PASS
- ✅ Error Handling Tests: PASS

### Test Metrics
- Total Tests Run: X
- Tests Passed: X
- Tests Failed: 0
- Code Coverage: X%

### Performance Metrics
- Average Response Time: Xms
- Average Query Time: Xms

## Breaking Changes
<List any breaking changes, or state "None">

## Migration Guide
<If breaking changes exist, provide migration guide>
<If no breaking changes, state "Not applicable">

## Documentation Updates
<List documentation that was updated>

- API documentation updated
- Database schema documentation updated
- Architecture documentation updated

## Screenshots/Logs
<Include relevant screenshots or log outputs if applicable>

## Notes
<Any important information reviewers should know>

- Special considerations
- Known limitations
- Future improvements
- Dependencies on other PRs

## Checklist
- [x] Code follows `coding-rules.md` standards
- [x] All tests passing
- [x] No critical or major issues
- [x] Service builds successfully
- [x] Service runs without errors
- [x] Documentation updated
- [x] PR description is complete and clear

## Related Issues
- Related Issue: #[issue-number]
- Depends On: #[pr-number]
- Closes: #[issue-number]

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

#### 7.2 PR Description Examples

**Example 1: Simple Feature Addition**

```markdown
## Task
Add job filtering functionality to the job search API

## Context
Users need the ability to filter jobs by status, location, and salary range
to find relevant opportunities more efficiently.

## Changes Implemented

### Added
- Job filtering by status (active, inactive, closed)
- Job filtering by location (city, state, remote)
- Job filtering by salary range (min, max)
- Pagination support for filtered results

### Modified
- `jobController.ts` - Added filter handling
- `jobService.ts` - Added filter logic
- `jobRepository.ts` - Added filtered queries

## Services Affected

### Primary Service
- **job-service** - Implemented filtering logic and API endpoints

## Files Modified

### New Files
- `harborJobSvc/validators/jobFilterValidators.ts` - Filter validation schemas

### Modified Files
- `harborJobSvc/controllers/jobController.ts` - Added getFilteredJobs method
- `harborJobSvc/services/jobService.ts` - Added filterJobs method
- `harborJobSvc/repositories/jobRepository.ts` - Added findByFilters method

## API Changes

### New Endpoints
- **GET /api/jobs/filter** - Search and filter jobs
  - Query Params: `status`, `location`, `salaryMin`, `salaryMax`, `page`, `limit`
  - Response: Paginated list of filtered jobs

## Testing Summary

### Test Results
- ✅ All 8 test categories passed
- ✅ 45/45 tests passed
- ✅ No issues found

### Performance Metrics
- Average Response Time: 12ms
- Average Query Time: 8ms
- With 3 filters: 15ms

## Breaking Changes
None

## Migration Guide
Not applicable

## Notes
- Filters are optional and composable
- Multiple filters can be combined
- Default pagination: 20 items per page, max 100

## Checklist
- [x] Code follows `coding-rules.md` standards
- [x] All tests passing
- [x] No critical or major issues
- [x] Documentation updated

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
```

